.TH eroosterctl-queue-list 1 "June 2026" "eroosterctl" "Erooster Manual"
.SH NAME
eroosterctl\-queue\-list \- list outbound queue entries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eroosterctl queue list
[\fI\-\-status\fR \fIstatus\fR]
[\fI\-\-output\fR \fBtable\fR|\fBjson\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Lists entries from the outbound mail queue. Without \fB\-\-status\fR, all
entries are shown. The table includes the entry ID, current status, attempt
count, sender, recipients, and most recent error (if any).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-status\fR \fIstatus\fR
Filter to entries with the specified status. One of: \fBpending\fR,
\fBdelivering\fR, \fBfailed\fR, \fBabandoned\fR, \fBdelivered\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fBtable\fR|\fBjson\fR
Output format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# Show all failed messages
eroosterctl queue list --status failed

# JSON for automated alerting
eroosterctl --output json queue list --status abandoned \
  | jq 'length'
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBeroosterctl\-queue\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-queue\-show\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-queue\-retry\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-queue\-flush\fR(1)
